          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>14065</commentid>
            <who name="Martin Wittemann">martin.wittemann</who>
            <bug_when>2009-11-12 09:53:48 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>For some scenarios, it would be nice to have an alternative loader template for example in a prefetch scenario. The easiest way to get that is to make a config key available, which defines the loader template to use during the build.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>14070</commentid>
            <who name="Thomas Herchenroeder">thron7</who>
            <bug_when>2009-11-12 11:11:59 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>The new config keys are

   compile-dist/paths/loader-template : &quot;&lt;path&gt;&quot;
   compile-source/loader-template : &quot;&lt;path&gt;&quot;

for build and source versions respectively.  &lt;path&gt; is a config-relative path, 
leading to a JS file that serves as a loader template. For details on possible 
macros and structure, see the standard template under 
tool/data/generator/loader.tmpl.js.

With r20608.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
